# Spec Rules

## Format
Every spec file MUST contain:
```yaml
id: <unique-id>
goal: <what this spec achieves>
constraints:
  - <constraint 1>
inputs:
  - <input 1>
outputs:
  - <output 1>
definition_of_done:
  - <testable criterion 1>
status: pending | ready | in_progress | done | failed
deps: [<spec-id>, ...]
priority: critical | high | medium | low
```

## Rules
- Specs are the ONLY source of truth for planning
- If a spec has >1 concern → split it
- If a spec is vague → split it
- If a spec touches >1 package → split it
- Specs reference other specs by id
- Status updates happen in spec files

## Naming
- `SPEC-XXX-short-description.yaml`
- Sequential numbering
- Grouped by domain in subdirectories when >20 specs
